{"id":9193,"date":"2025-11-20T04:45:42","date_gmt":"2025-11-20T04:45:42","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/realtrips.in\/?post_type=trip&#038;p=9193"},"modified":"2025-11-20T07:02:58","modified_gmt":"2025-11-20T07:02:58","slug":"shimla-manali-chandigarh-2","status":"publish","type":"trip","link":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/trip\/shimla-manali-chandigarh-2\/","title":{"rendered":"SHIMLA MANALI CHANDIGARH"},"content":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","template":"","destination":[120],"activities":[],"trip_types":[118],"difficulty":[],"trip_tag":[],"wptravelengine_custom_taxonomy_tripcategory":[81],"class_list":["post-9193","trip","type-trip","status-publish","hentry","destination-magical-himachal-special-2","trip_types-domestic-group-tour","tripcategory-group-domestic-tour"],"packages_ids":[9291],"trip_extras":[],"cut_off_time":{"enabled":false,"duration":0,"duration_unit":"days"},"booked-seats":[],"code":"WTE-9193","price":45000,"has_sale":false,"sale_price":0,"discount_percent":0,"currency":{"code":"INR","symbol":"&#8377;"},"duration":{"days":7,"nights":6,"duration_unit":"days","duration_type":"days"},"min_pax":1,"max_pax":"","discount_value":0,"discount_label":"&#8377;0 Off","primary_category":27,"available_times":{"type":"default","items":["2021-1-01","2021-2-01","2021-3-01","2021-4-01","2021-5-01","2021-6-01","2021-7-01","2021-8-01","2021-9-01","2021-10-01","2021-11-01","2021-12-01"]},"description":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Shimla, Manali, and Chandigarh<\/strong> are a popular trio of destinations in northern India, each offering unique experiences. <strong>Shimla<\/strong>, the \"Queen of Hills,\" is known for its colonial charm, pleasant weather, and scenic beauty. Visitors can stroll along Mall Road, explore Jakhoo Temple, or enjoy activities in Kufri. <strong>Manali<\/strong>, a paradise for adventure lovers, boasts snow-capped mountains, thrilling sports, and attractions like Solang Valley, Rohtang Pass, and the Hidimba Temple. Lastly, <strong>Chandigarh<\/strong>, India\u2019s first planned city, blends modernity with nature. It features attractions like the Rock Garden, Sukhna Lake, and Rose Garden, offering a peaceful and vibrant escape. Together, these destinations provide a perfect mix of adventure, relaxation, and culture.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->","cost_includes":"3 Star Hotel Accommodation as per the appointed Room.\nAll transfers and sightseeing by Vehicle Ex Delhi Ex Chandigard\nReturn Economy Airfare Pune - Pune \nBreakfast, Lunch Dinner as per mention itinerary   \nExperience Tour manager throughout Tour.\nTravel insurance\nEvening Tea and Coffee\nAll Entry Fees\nDaily 1 Ltr water Bottle per person  \nToll Tax.\nParking.\nDriver Allowance. \nTravel Goodies","cost_excludes":"Any meals other than those mentioned above included.\nGST 5%\nRohatang snow Point \/Kufri pony Ride or Union Vehicle\nSport activity Rafting, Paragliding, Snow jacket (Gamboot)\nAny portage at airports and hotels, tips, insurance, wine, mineral water, telephone charges, and all  items of personal nature.\nAny services not specifically mentioned in the inclusions.\nEntrance fees to Monuments & other sight-seeing points.\nExpenses caused by factors beyond our control like rail and flight delays, roadblocks, vehicle mal-                   functions, political disturbances etc.\nAnything Not mentioned in inclusions","itineraries":[],"faqs":[{"title":"1.What is the best time to visit Shimla, Manali, and Chandigarh?","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The best time to visit is during the summer months (March to June) for pleasant weather. If you want to experience snow, December to February is ideal.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"2.How far are Shimla, Manali, and Chandigarh from each other?","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Shimla to Manali: 250 km (approx. 7-8 hours by road)<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Manali to Chandigarh: 310 km (approx. 8-9 hours by road)<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Shimla to Chandigarh: 120 km (approx. 3-4 hours by road)<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"3.What are the must-see attractions in Shimla?","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Ridge, Mall Road, Jakhoo Temple, Kufri, Christ Church, and the Kalka-Shimla Railway.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"4.What are the must-visit places in Manali?","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Solang Valley, Rohtang Pass, Hidimba Temple, Old Manali, and the Manali Mall Road.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"5.What are the best adventure activities to do in Shimla and Manali?","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In Shimla: Skiing, paragliding, and hiking.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In Manali: Skiing, rafting, trekking, paragliding, and zorbing.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"}],"is_featured":false,"featured_image":{},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/trip\/9193","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/trip"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/trip"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=9193"}],"version-history":[{"count":3,"href":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/trip\/9193\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":9202,"href":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/trip\/9193\/revisions\/9202"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=9193"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"destination","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity